487
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:36,600
Landscape.

488
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:37,700
Alright, you walk in front.

489
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:45,733
Are you taking a picture or...

490
00:25:45,733 --> 00:25:47,200
What are you doing?

491
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:49,800
Done taking the picture.

492
00:25:51,067 --> 00:25:52,367
How nice, how magical.

493
00:25:59,300 --> 00:25:59,733
Where am I?

494
00:25:59,733 --> 00:26:01,600
Are you taking a picture of me or the tourists?

495
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:02,633
Where am I?

496
00:26:03,067 --> 00:26:04,033
Bro, let me tell you.

497
00:26:04,033 --> 00:26:05,500
I'll teach you how to frame the shot.

498
00:26:07,167 --> 00:26:09,400
Alright, that's basically it.

499
00:26:10,267 --> 00:26:11,467
Don't get too far from me.

500
00:26:11,467 --> 00:26:12,267
Just make sure I'm...

501
00:26:12,267 --> 00:26:14,233
a little closer to your phone.

502
00:26:14,233 --> 00:26:17,100
And my feet should be closer to the bottom of the frame.

503
00:26:17,633 --> 00:26:19,167
That's pretty much it.

504
00:26:19,433 --> 00:26:21,133
I'm not good at taking pictures either.

505
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,367
Do I look like a bear right now?

506
00:26:25,367 --> 00:26:26,300
This really is you.

507
00:26:27,067 --> 00:26:28,533
This is really just you, right?

508
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:30,433
This one's good.

509
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:32,733
No.

510
00:26:32,733 --> 00:26:35,067
